   <text>
      <front>
         <div1 n="1" type="abstract">
            <head>
               <bibl>
                  <abbr>ALS</abbr>
                  <extent>16 pp.</extent>
                  <date>Autumn 1863</date>
                  <idno rend="suppress">SPEC.MMS.138_4</idno>
                  <title>Letter from Sophia Hawthorne to Elizabeth Palmer Peabody</title>
               </bibl>
            </head>
            <p>Sophia writes about the economic hardships the family is going through, Rose's current (and Una's past) development through adolescence, and a quarrel with her sister, Mary, about some books.</p>
         </div1>
      </front>
      <body>
         <div1 n="1" type="letter">
            <head></head>
            
<!-- Page 1 -->
<pb mmid="/a/a0583997-80b3-449c-ae3e-96caf2f38a87" n="1"/>

            <opener>
               <seg>
                  <figure>
                     <figDesc>Rusty paper clip</figDesc>
                  </figure>
               </seg>
<lb/><seg><figure><head>Stationer's mark. SPEC.MMS.138 Letter4_P1.jpg</head><figDesc><xref url="a0583997-80b3-449c-ae3e-96caf2f38a87?qlt=92&amp;effect=dropshadow,000000,50,8,120,8&amp;RGN=0.053,0.873,0.119,0.086&amp;cell=500,500&amp;effect=text,">[Stationer's mark (click to open image in a new window)]</xref>Stationer's mark, SPEC.MMS.138, Letter4_P1.jpg</figDesc></figure></seg><lb/> 
<lb id="L04L001" n="001"/>
            <dateline>
                  <date>Sunday</date>
               </dateline>
               
<lb id="L04L002" n="002"/>
               <salute>My dear <name reg="Peabody, Elizabeth Palmer" type="recipient">Elizabeth</name>
                  <seg>
                     <note target="n1">1</note>
                  </seg>
               </salute>, I have
               </opener>

<p>
               
<lb id="L04L003" n="003"/> become so occupied with 
<lb id="L04L004" n="004"/>
               <rs>the unhappy Weiss</rs>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n2">2</note>
               </seg>, that 
<lb id="L04L005" n="005"/> with my necessary household 
<lb id="L04L006" n="006"/> cares, mending &amp; making &mdash;
<lb id="L04L007" n="007"/> I have not had one 
<lb id="L04L008" n="008"/> moment to answer your 
<lb id="L04L009" n="009"/> note. It is Sunday and 
<lb id="L04L010" n="010"/> all the children are at 
<lb id="L04L011" n="011"/> Church<seg>
                  <note target="n3">3</note>
               </seg>, and I have a 
<lb id="L04L012" n="012"/> few moments of my own &mdash;
<lb id="L04L013" n="013"/> and out of a hundred 
<lb id="L04L014" n="014"/> things I want to do, I 
<lb id="L04L015" n="015"/> take some <add hand="SPH" place="supralinear" rend="caret">time</add> for you. 
<lb id="L04L016" n="016"/> We could not take 
<lb id="L04L017" n="017"/> advantage of the free
<lb id="L04L018" n="018"/> lessons of <name reg="">
                  <abbr expan="Doctor">Dr.</abbr> Kinner</name>
<lb id="L04L019" n="019"/> for <name reg="Hawthorne, Una">Una</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n4">4</note>
               </seg>, on account

<lb id="L04L020" n="020"/> partly <del hand="SPH" type="overwritten">and</del>of the expense 
<lb id="L04L021" n="021"/> of railroad fare &mdash; while 
<lb id="L04L022" n="022"/> there were other reasons 
<lb id="L04L023" n="023"/>less imperative. I am very sorry, but <seg>
                  <note target="nstar">*</note>
               </seg>

<!-- Page 2 -->
<pb mmid="/9/9bc802ea-2b10-4095-97ab-c4435c71ece8" n="2"/>
               
<lb id="L04L024" n="024"/> since there is not 
<lb id="L04L025" n="025"/> literally money enough 
<lb id="L04L026" n="026"/> for it &mdash; I accept the 
<lb id="L04L027" n="027"/> disappointment. For it 
<lb id="L04L028" n="028"/> is certainly a very plain 
<lb id="L04L029" n="029"/> duty not to spend other

<lb id="L04L030" n="030"/> peoples' money for 
<lb id="L04L031" n="031"/> accomplishments &mdash; <add hand="SPH" place="infralinear">^</add><add hand="SPH" place="supralinear">or any thing else</add>. And as 
<lb id="L04L032" n="032"/> we are very closely pressed 
<lb id="L04L033" n="033"/> this year &mdash; and feel it 
<lb id="L04L034" n="034"/> important not to grind 
<lb id="L04L035" n="035"/>
               <name reg="Hawthorne, Julian">Julian</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n5">5</note>
               </seg> too closely in

<lb id="L04L036" n="036"/>
               <name reg="Harvard College" type="place">college</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n6">6</note>
               </seg>, (though he must 
<lb id="L04L037" n="037"/> be exceedingly economical 
<lb id="L04L038" n="038"/> at the best) &mdash; we must 
<lb id="L04L039" n="039"/> all sacrifice a great 
<lb id="L04L040" n="040"/> many pleasant things. 
<lb id="L04L041" n="041"/> If <name reg="Hawthorne, Nathaniel">
                  <abbr expan="Mister">Mr</abbr> Hawthorne</name> did <seg>
                  <note target="ndagger">&#134;</note>
               </seg>
               
<lb id="L04L042" n="042"/> not write, we could by 
<lb id="L04L043" n="043"/> no means make our 
<lb id="L04L044" n="044"/> expenses come within 
<lb id="L04L045" n="045"/> our income, and 
<lb id="L04L046" n="046"/> it is a pain to him

<lb id="L04L047" n="047"/> to be so hard driven 
<seg>
                  <note target="nstar">*</note>
</seg>

<!-- Page 3 -->
<pb mmid="/8/81cfa20f-fc28-4912-8cfe-e448407f348e" n="3"/>
               
<lb id="L04L048" n="048"/> in his present unenergetic 
<lb id="L04L049" n="049"/> condition, and he 
<lb id="L04L050" n="050"/> doubts if we can <add hand="SPH" place="supralinear" rend="caret">at any rate</add>
<lb id="L04L051" n="051"/> easily make the ends 
<lb id="L04L052" n="052"/> meet. The Smiths have
<lb id="L04L053" n="053"/> sent for <name reg="Hawthorne, Una">Una</name> and <name reg="Hawthorne, Julian">Julian</name>
<lb id="L04L054" n="054"/> to go to see them this 
<lb id="L04L055" n="055"/> winter. But for the 
<lb id="L04L056" n="056"/> same reason, they cannot 
<lb id="L04L057" n="057"/> go. It would cost at 
<lb id="L04L058" n="058"/> least thirty dollars for 
<lb id="L04L059" n="059"/> travel from our door to theirs, and 
<lb id="L04L060" n="060"/>
               <name reg="Hawthorne, Julian"> Julian</name> would have to 
<lb id="L04L061" n="061"/> have a new suit of 
<lb id="L04L062" n="062"/> clothes &mdash; costing thirty
<lb id="L04L063" n="063"/>more &mdash; before he could
<lb id="L04L064" n="064"/>go. As to me, I am 
<lb id="L04L065" n="065"/> going without any 
<lb id="L04L066" n="066"/> thing new whatever 
<lb id="L04L067" n="067"/> and I only wish I could 
<lb id="L04L068" n="068"/> give up any thing more	
<lb id="L04L069" n="069"/> so as to gratify <seg>
                  <note target="nstar">*</note>
               </seg>
<lb id="L04L070" n="070"/> them. As to their father

<!-- Page 4 -->
<pb mmid="/b/bdbdbb87-3f55-4b1d-850e-b05c92bd7492" n="4"/>
               
<lb id="L04L071" n="071"/> he is a perfect <name reg="Diogenes of Sinope">Diogenes</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n7">7</note>
               </seg>
               
<lb id="L04L072" n="072"/> or a god &mdash; about going 
<lb id="L04L073" n="073"/> without things. He will 
<lb id="L04L074" n="074"/> not allow himself the 
<lb id="L04L075" n="075"/> smallest expenditure. 
<lb id="L04L076" n="076"/>
               <name reg="Hawthorne, Julian"> Julian</name> has had expensive 
<lb id="L04L077" n="077"/> books stolen by some 
<lb id="L04L078" n="078"/> <sic corr="thieves">theives</sic> among the 
<lb id="L04L079" n="079"/> Sophomores &mdash; one very 
<lb id="L04L080" n="080"/>immense Greek Lexicon, 
<lb id="L04L081" n="081"/> what I should think 
<lb id="L04L082" n="082"/> must have cost five 
<lb id="L04L083" n="083"/> dollars at least. 
<lb id="L04L084" n="084"/>
               <name reg="Gurney, Ephraim"> Professor Gurney</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n8">8</note>
               </seg> says <q>this 
<lb id="L04L085" n="085"/> is one of the dirtiest 
<lb id="L04L086" n="086"/> of their dirty tricks</q> and 
<lb id="L04L087" n="087"/> that there is no redress. 
<lb id="L04L088" n="088"/>
               <name reg="Hawthorne, Julian"> Julian</name> gets along 
<lb id="L04L089" n="089"/> splendidly as a brave 
<lb id="L04L090" n="090"/> and gentle <add hand="Unknown" place="supralinear" rend="upsidedown">Dear Sir</add> and stalwart 
<lb id="L04L091" n="091"/> knight. A gentleman 
<lb id="L04L092" n="092"/> told me he was looked 
<lb id="L04L093" n="093"/> upon as a powerful 
<lb id="L04L094" n="094"/> lion &mdash; and one <add hand="SPH" place="supralinear" rend="caret">of</add> his 
<lb id="L04L095" n="095"/>
               <del hand="SPH" type="">a</del>names is <q>the Immortal 
<lb id="L04L096" n="096"/> Hawthorne.</q> He makes no

<!-- Page 5 -->
<pb mmid="/9/9fe1b3e8-f5b0-4502-8771-655cda41e985" n="5"/>
 
<fw place="top of the page" type="sig">2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi></fw>
<lb id="L04L097" n="097"/> aggression, but  
<lb id="L04L098" n="098"/>defends the weak &mdash; <seg>
                  <note target="nstar">*</note>
               </seg>
               
<lb id="L04L099" n="099"/> and no one dares to
<lb id="L04L100" n="100"/> touch him &mdash; as they 
<lb id="L04L101" n="101"/> all know him strong &mdash;
<lb id="L04L102" n="102"/> and find him valiant.
<lb id="L04L103" n="103"/> He has not a particle 
<lb id="L04L104" n="104"/> of low, unchristian vindic <seg type="softhyphen">&dash;</seg>
<lb id="L04L105" n="105"/> tiveness in his nature &mdash;
<lb id="L04L106" n="106"/> They make broad 
<lb id="L04L107" n="107"/> lanes for him to pass
<lb id="L04L108" n="108"/> when they think he
<lb id="L04L109" n="109"/> might revenge some
<lb id="L04L110" n="110"/> classmate's wrong &mdash; 
<lb id="L04L111" n="111"/> and treat him personally
<lb id="L04L112" n="112"/> with high respect and
<lb id="L04L113" n="113"/> the good, gentlemanly 
<lb id="L04L114" n="114"/> Sophomores are his
<lb id="L04L115" n="115"/> friends. But if I tell
<lb id="L04L116" n="116"/> you so much, you will
<lb id="L04L117" n="117"/> say I am making a 
<lb id="L04L118" n="118"/> fine story and praising
<lb id="L04L119" n="119"/> him too much. It is a 
<lb id="L04L120" n="120"/> pity I cannot talk to
<lb id="L04L121" n="121"/> a sister without that
<lb id="L04L122" n="122"/> suspicion &mdash; <sic corr="isn't">is n't</sic> it?

<!-- Page 6 -->
<pb mmid="/6/60f9c56e-23e5-47d5-948c-5118dc89b964" n="6"/>
               
<lb id="L04L123" n="123"/> When I do not answer <seg>
                  <note target="nstar">*</note>
               </seg>
<lb id="L04L124" n="124"/> your notes, dear <name reg="Peabody, Elizabeth Palmer">Elizabeth </name>
<lb id="L04L125" n="125"/> sometimes, it is not
<lb id="L04L126" n="126"/> because I accept
<lb id="L04L127" n="127"/> them, but because I
<lb id="L04L128" n="128"/> disagree, and think it
<lb id="L04L129" n="129"/> of no use to discuss
<lb id="L04L130" n="130"/> the matter. Some things
<lb id="L04L131" n="131"/> in that long ago note
<lb id="L04L132" n="132"/> I agreed with, however &mdash;
<lb id="L04L133" n="133"/>
               <name reg="Hawthorne, Rose">Rose's</name> face expresses too
<lb id="L04L134" n="134"/> much critical displeasure
<lb id="L04L135" n="135"/> I very well see often.
<lb id="L04L136" n="136"/> She is in precisely the
<lb id="L04L137" n="137"/> mood that <name reg="Hawthorne, Une">Una</name> was
<lb id="L04L138" n="138"/> in at her age in <name reg="Rock Ferry" type="place">Rock
<lb id="L04L139" n="139"/> Ferry</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n9">9</note>
               </seg>. <name reg="Hawthorne, Une">Una</name> was then
<lb id="L04L140" n="140"/> disgusted with every body 
<lb id="L04L141" n="141"/> and thing that did not 
<lb id="L04L142" n="142"/> suit her taste &amp; principles
<lb id="L04L143" n="143"/> and seemed to fail
<lb id="L04L144" n="144"/> utterly in <abbr expan="Saint">St</abbr> Paul's 
<lb id="L04L145" n="145"/> Charity<seg>
                  <note target="n10">10</note>
               </seg>. I was quite
               
<!-- Page 7 -->
<pb mmid="/3/3da2a08c-a51d-465f-8f22-099c2f6c6f7a" n="7"/>
               
<lb id="L04L146" n="146"/> alarmed, until a certain <seg>
                  <note target="nstar">*</note>
               </seg>
<lb id="L04L147" n="147"/>
               <abbr expan="Mistress">Mrs.</abbr>
               <name reg="Allbut">Allbut</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n11">11</note>
               </seg> told me
<lb id="L04L148" n="148"/> that I need not fear
<lb id="L04L149" n="149"/> at all, for that when
<lb id="L04L150" n="150"/>
               <name reg="Hawthorne, Una">Una</name> was eighteen she
<lb id="L04L151" n="151"/> would be all right, and
<lb id="L04L152" n="152"/> that this fastidiousness
<lb id="L04L153" n="153"/> at her age was the
<lb id="L04L154" n="154"/> most hopeful of all
<lb id="L04L155" n="155"/> states. I find it true.
<lb id="L04L156" n="156"/>
               <name reg="Hawthorne, Una">Una</name> is always excusing
<lb id="L04L157" n="157"/> every body now, and 
<lb id="L04L158" n="158"/> finding good points
<lb id="L04L159" n="159"/> in every one, and no
<lb id="L04L160" n="160"/> soul is more full of
<lb id="L04L161" n="161"/> generous, self sacrificing
<lb id="L04L162" n="162"/> love. Every person I
<lb id="L04L163" n="163"/> know in <name reg="Concord, Massachusetts" type="place">Concord</name>
<lb id="L04L164" n="164"/> bursts out to me about
<lb id="L04L165" n="165"/> her in enthusiastic
<lb id="L04L166" n="166"/> praise &mdash; not moderate 
<lb id="L04L167" n="167"/> but enthusiastic praise.
<lb id="L04L168" n="168"/> You get all your evil
<lb id="L04L169" n="169"/>
               <sic corr="impressions">impressons</sic> of her
               
<!-- Page 8 -->
<pb mmid="/5/51b98994-23c6-4481-a15f-c59ed31acb4b" n="8"/>
               
<lb id="L04L170" n="170"/> from the <name reg="Alcott">Alcotts</name> probably, <seg>
                  <note target="nstar">*</note>
               </seg>
<lb id="L04L171" n="171"/> as no one else maligns 
<lb id="L04L172" n="172"/> her. Mrs 
               <name reg="Emerson">Emerson</name>, all
<lb id="L04L173" n="173"/> the <name reg="Emerson">Emersons</name>, the 
<lb id="L04L174" n="174"/>
               <name reg="Pritchard">Pritchards</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n12">12</note>
               </seg>, the <name reg="MacKay">MacKays</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n13">13</note>
               </seg>,
<lb id="L04L175" n="175"/> the <name reg="Hoars">Hoars</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n14">14</note>
               </seg>, the all
<lb id="L04L176" n="176"/> the world of <name reg="Concord, Massachusetts" type="place">Concord</name>
<lb id="L04L177" n="177"/> agree in love to her.
<lb id="L04L178" n="178"/> They call her <q>loveliest</q>
<lb id="L04L179" n="179"/>
               <q>the most devoted</q>
               <q>the
<lb id="L04L180" n="180"/> most generous</q> and
<lb id="L04L181" n="181"/> all sorts of pretty names.
<lb id="L04L182" n="182"/>
               <name reg="Hawthorne, Rose">Miss Rose</name> deserves your
<lb id="L04L183" n="183"/> censure, but as she
<lb id="L04L184" n="184"/> has a world of adoring
<lb id="L04L185" n="185"/> love in her, I hope she
<lb id="L04L186" n="186"/> will <unclear reason="obscured by ink stain" rend="">soon</unclear>love all 
<lb id="L04L187" n="187"/> her fellow creatures
<lb id="L04L188" n="188"/> as she now loves
<lb id="L04L189" n="189"/> some of them. I
<lb id="L04L190" n="190"/> talk with her a great &mdash;
<lb id="L04L191" n="191"/> deal about the propriety 
<lb id="L04L192" n="192"/> of feeling genial and 
<lb id="L04L193" n="193"/> pleased in society &mdash;
<lb id="L04L194" n="194"/> and I shall continue to

<!-- Page 9 -->
<pb mmid="/6/6ba80fb7-3718-4fbd-b96f-ddd8e5886b45" n="9"/>

<fw place="top of the page" type="sig">3<hi rend="superscript">d</hi></fw>
<lb id="L04L0195" n="195"/> adjure her.  But 
               <seg>
                  <note target="nstar">*</note>
               </seg>
<lb id="L04L196" n="196"/> I do not doubt she 
<lb id="L04L197" n="197"/> will be a loving and 
<lb id="L04L198" n="198"/> gracious person. For
<lb id="L04L199" n="199"/> you do not know what 
<lb id="L04L200" n="200"/> a power of generosity 
<lb id="L04L201" n="201"/> she has &mdash; and all in
<lb id="L04L202" n="202"/> the true Christ<abbr expan="ian">&mdash;</abbr> spirit 
<lb id="L04L203" n="203"/> of not letting the right 
<lb id="L04L204" n="204"/> hand know &amp; c. For 
<lb id="L04L205" n="205"/> this is one thing they
<lb id="L04L206" n="206"/> were born with as 
<lb id="L04L207" n="207"/> I have brought out &mdash;
<lb id="L04L208" n="208"/> to make no show of 
<lb id="L04L209" n="209"/> any thing they can 
<lb id="L04L210" n="210"/> do or feel . . . They are 
<lb id="L04L212" n="212"/> genuine &amp; and all 
<lb id="L04L213" n="213"/> as true as heaven itself. 
<lb id="L04L214" n="214"/> Oh dear &mdash; now I am 
<lb id="L04L215" n="215"/> off on this eulogistic 
<lb id="L04L216" n="216"/> track. But really if 
<lb id="L04L217" n="217"/> you lived with them 
<lb id="L04L218" n="218"/> you would not love 
<lb id="L04L219" n="219"/> them little. And if 
<lb id="L04L220" n="220"/> you could see how <name reg="Hawthorne, Julian"> Julian's </name>

<!-- Page 10 -->
<pb mmid="/b/bd6db89f-fc0f-49ce-851c-42ee4fe48427" n="10"/>
               
<lb id="L04L221" n="221"/> innocence is becoming 
<lb id="L04L223" n="223"/> virtue, you would be 
<lb id="L04L224" n="224"/> glad as I am; and
<lb id="L04L225" n="225"/> overflow sometimes. 
<lb id="L04L226" n="226"/> Religious principle is 
<lb id="L04L227" n="227"/> the only sure guard
<lb id="L04L228" n="228"/> angelic, and I am sure 
<lb id="L04L229" n="229"/> they all have it. They 
<lb id="L04L230" n="230"/> are all reverent. 
<lb id="L04L231" n="231"/> I think a cultivated 
<lb id="L04L232" n="232"/> imagination and a 
<lb id="L04L233" n="233"/> delicate &mdash; or <sic corr="not smothered">unsmothered</sic>
<lb id="L04L234" n="234"/> conscience are the diamond 
<lb id="L04L235" n="235"/> shield against evil. 
<lb id="L04L236" n="236"/>
               <name reg="Hawthorne, Julian">Julian's</name> memory scintillates 
<lb id="L04L237" n="237"/> with high, heroic thoughts 
<lb id="L04L238" n="238"/> and deeds. His father 
<lb id="L04L239" n="239"/> put into him, reading 
<lb id="L04L240" n="240"/> aloud, every noble story 
<lb id="L04L241" n="241"/> of literature. He has 
<lb id="L04L242" n="242"/> therefore kept the 
<lb id="L04L243" n="243"/> highest society &mdash; and 
<lb id="L04L244" n="244"/> has no love for

<!-- Page 11 -->
<pb mmid="/7/7bb7c439-45f5-4da7-b3e9-347a9713e1a9" n="11"/>
               
<lb id="L04L245" n="245"/> low persons &mdash; no <seg>
                  <note target="nstar">*</note>
               </seg>
<lb id="L04L246" n="246"/> tastes that are ignoble. 
<lb id="L04L247" n="247"/> But I will stop this 
<lb id="L04L248" n="248"/> talk &mdash; whether or no. 
<lb id="L04L249" n="249"/> Who told the <name reg="Mann, Mary Tyler Peabody">Queen of 
<lb id="L04L250" n="250"/> the Angels</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n15">15</note>
               </seg> that I 
<lb id="L04L251" n="251"/> complained about the 
<lb id="L04L252" n="252"/> injury of the books? I 
<lb id="L04L253" n="253"/> did not &mdash; and I never 
<lb id="L04L254" n="254"/> asked any one to tell 
<lb id="L04L255" n="255"/> her &mdash; I never thought it 
<lb id="L04L256" n="256"/> owing to her carelessness &mdash;
<lb id="L04L257" n="257"/> for I know she is 
<lb id="L04L258" n="258"/> never careless. But 
<lb id="L04L259" n="259"/> all the fly leaves were 
<lb id="L04L260" n="260"/> torn out up to the
<lb id="L04L261" n="261"/> very commencement 
<lb id="L04L262" n="262"/> of the text in very 
<lb id="L04L263" n="263"/> many. It seemed as 
<lb id="L04L264" n="264"/> if they were torn out 
<lb id="L04L265" n="265"/> for waste paper. 
<lb id="L04L266" n="266"/> Somebody did it &mdash; but 
<lb id="L04L267" n="267"/> I never supposed

<!-- Page 12 -->
<pb mmid="/a/a8d4e8bf-e170-4f57-afec-85b722dc2118" n="12"/>
               
<lb id="L04L268" n="268"/>
               <name reg="Mann, Mary Tyler Peabody">Margaret</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n16">16</note>
               </seg>allowed
<lb id="L04L269" n="269"/> it or knew of it.
<lb id="L04L270" n="270"/> She will not be so
<lb id="L04L271" n="271"/> angry therefore with
<lb id="L04L272" n="272"/> me &mdash; who sent her no
<lb id="L04L273" n="273"/> reproach nor message
<lb id="L04L274" n="274"/> and would have
<lb id="L04L275" n="275"/> forbidden anyone to
<lb id="L04L276" n="276"/> say a word to her &mdash;
<lb id="L04L277" n="277"/> she will not punish
<lb id="L04L278" n="278"/> me, so innocent, by
<lb id="L04L279" n="279"/> never borrowing
<lb id="L04L280" n="280"/> another book from me!
<lb id="L04L281" n="281"/> And she too, the <name reg="Mann, Mary Tyler Peabody">Queen
<lb id="L04L282" n="282"/> of the Angels</name>! Tell
<lb id="L04L283" n="283"/> her then to lay off her
<lb id="L04L284" n="284"/> crown, for she is not
<lb id="L04L285" n="285"/> the <foreign lang="lat">Regina angelorum</foreign>
<lb id="L04L286" n="286"/> any longer. I wish
<lb id="L04L287" n="287"/> folk would leave me
<lb id="L04L288" n="288"/> to do my own fault &mdash; 
<lb id="L04L289" n="289"/> finding &mdash; my own duty, in
<lb id="L04L290" n="290"/> short &mdash; and not try to do it for me

<!-- Page 13 -->
<pb mmid="/0/04b67535-74ea-4328-96ba-b87d4e0bf736" n="13"/>

<fw type="sig" place="top of the page">4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></fw>
<lb id="L04L291" n="291"/> The reason I do not
<lb id="L04L292" n="292"/> fancy <name reg="Pugh, ??">Mrs Pugh</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n17">17</note>
               </seg> is because
<lb id="L04L293" n="293"/> she disenchanted herself
<lb id="L04L294" n="294"/> by her artificialness and
<lb id="L04L295" n="295"/> an effect of unveritable
<lb id="L04L296" n="296"/>ness. At first I went
<lb id="L04L297" n="297"/> upon your impression
<lb id="L04L298" n="298"/> of her, and your talk of
<lb id="L04L299" n="299"/> her to me. But very
<lb id="L04L300" n="300"/> soon she became
<lb id="L04L301" n="301"/>
               <unclear rend="" resp="" cert="" hand="SPH">oppressive</unclear> and sultry
<lb id="L04L302" n="302"/> and not genuine to
<lb id="L04L303" n="303"/> me. And I declare I
<lb id="L04L304" n="304"/> cannot help this.
<lb id="L04L305" n="305"/> It is her fault, not
<lb id="L04L306" n="306"/> mine. No reasoning
<lb id="L04L307" n="307"/> no developments of
<lb id="L04L308" n="308"/> her life will help it.
<lb id="L04L309" n="309"/> Every person must stand
<lb id="L04L310" n="310"/> or fall upon their character
<lb id="L04L311" n="311"/> as evidenced by their
<lb id="L04L312" n="312"/> presences.  It is a
<lb id="L04L313" n="313"/> law of the universe
<lb id="L04L314" n="314"/> and no talk will alter it.
<!-- Page 14 -->
<pb mmid="/e/ee010eb9-0bcb-464c-8191-a8b8a867093b" n="14"/>
               
<lb id="L04L315" n="315"/> I take a fancy to
<lb id="L04L316" n="316"/>
               <name reg="Turner, Mr. and Mrs.">Mr. &amp; Mrs. Turner
               </name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n18">18</note>
               </seg>, of
<lb id="L04L317" n="317"/> whom you speak very
<lb id="L04L318" n="318"/>
               <unclear rend="" reason="" resp="" cert="" hand="SPH">Sneeringly</unclear> because they
<lb id="L04L319" n="319"/> are single, simple, true,
<lb id="L04L320" n="320"/> lovely and refined &mdash;
<lb id="L04L321" n="321"/> These are very good
<lb id="L04L322" n="322"/> reasons, and very good
<lb id="L04L323" n="323"/> qualities.</p><p>
<lb id="L04L324" n="324"/> I am sorry I have
<lb id="L04L325" n="325"/> no drawings for your
<lb id="L04L326" n="326"/> babies this week.
<lb id="L04L327" n="327"/> But I have been
<lb id="L04L328" n="328"/>
               <sic corr="overwhelmed">overwhemed</sic>since
<lb id="L04L329" n="329"/> the suicide of <name reg="Weis, Adelaide"> Adelaide
<lb id="L04L330" n="330"/> Weis</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n19">19</note>
               </seg> with cares
<lb id="L04L331" n="331"/> for the rest of them &mdash;
<lb id="L04L332" n="332"/> I have had to 
<lb id="L04L333" n="333"/> neglect many things &mdash;
<lb id="L04L334" n="334"/> not however so imperative

<!-- Page 15 -->
<pb mmid="/b/bd063794-051a-4f33-bfb1-4fde84df2e22" n="15"/>
 
               <figure>
                  <figDesc>stationer's mark.</figDesc>
               </figure>
               
<lb id="L04L335" n="335"/> as their needs.</p><p>
<lb id="L04L336" n="336"/> I have the comfort of
<lb id="L04L337" n="337"/> a perfect peace and
<lb id="L04L338" n="338"/> order &amp; intelligence
<lb id="L04L339" n="339"/> in the kitchen &mdash; for
<lb id="L04L340" n="340"/> which I am most
<lb id="L04L341" n="341"/> thankful &mdash; for I
<lb id="L04L342" n="342"/> dreaded <name reg="???, Ann"> Ann's</name>
               <seg>
                  <note target="n20">20</note>
               </seg> going
<lb id="L04L343" n="343"/> to <name reg="California" type="place">California</name>&mdash; away
<lb id="L04L344" n="344"/> from me.  There are
<lb id="L04L345" n="345"/> other treasures, I
<lb id="L04L346" n="346"/> find among the
<lb id="L04L347" n="347"/>
               <unclear rend="" reason="" resp="" cert="" hand="SPH">Irish</unclear> besides her.
<lb id="L04L348" n="348"/> Indeed I knew this
<lb id="L04L349" n="349"/> but feared not to
<lb id="L04L350" n="350"/> become possessed
<lb id="L04L351" n="351"/> of them.</p><p>
<lb id="L04L352" n="352"/> I hope you are very
<lb id="L04L353" n="353"/> well and that the
<lb id="L04L354" n="354"/>
               <name reg="Mann, Mary Tyler Peabody">Queen of the Angels</name>
<lb id="L04L355" n="355"/> is well this autumn.

<!-- Page 16 -->
<pb mmid="/3/3ca8f540-0f9b-4bf4-ab05-32caad1a23bd" n="16"/>
               
<lb id="L04L356" n="356"/> Give my love to
<lb id="L04L357" n="357"/> her.
</p>
            <closer>
                <lb id="L04L358" n="358"/> Ever yours, 
                <lb id="L04L359" n="359"/><signed>
                  <name type="sender">Sophia</name>
               </signed>
               <add hand="Unknown" place="right margin">Mrs. Hawthorne</add>
            </closer>
